Global Storage as a Service (SaaS) Market

The storage as a service (SaaS) market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 30.82% in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. Data Bridge Market Research report on storage as a service (SaaS) market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth. The rise in end user verticals globally is escalating the growth of storage as a service (SaaS) market.

Storage as a Service, also known as hosted storage, refers to a business model where a company usually rents or leases its storage infrastructure to another individuals or company for storage of data. Small companies and individuals often adopt the service as it is considered a suitable method for managing backups, while providing cost savings in hardware, personnel, and physical space.

The surge in data consumptions among organizations across the globe acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of storage as a service (SaaS) market. The increased use of mobile devices such as smartphones and tablets by customers and employees, and rise in need for data archiving accelerate the market growth. The availability of cost-effective services and cutting-edge expertise rendered by data servicing companies, and high adoption of the service as it is cost effective and reduces risks in disaster recovery further influence the market. Additionally, rise in the adoption of Internet of things, increase system availability, huge amounts of data generated, rapid digitization, and integration of advanced technologies positively affect the storage as a service (SaaS) market. Furthermore, increased adoption of archive as a service, and emergence of cloud-based storage gateways extend profitable opportunities to the market players in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029.

On the other hand, issues associated with bandwidth and interoperative limitations are expected to obstruct the market growth. Privacy and security concerns are projected to challenge the storage as a service (SaaS) market in the forecast period of 2022-2029.

